Write the equals method in the Vertex class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class Vertex {
    equals(otherVertex) {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```
class Vertex {
    equals(otherVertex) {
        if (otherVertex == null) return false;
        const tolerance = 1e-8;
        return (
          Math.abs(this.x - otherVertex.x) < tolerance &&
          Math.abs(this.y - otherVertex.y) < tolerance &&
          Math.abs(this.z - otherVertex.z) < tolerance
        );
    }
}
```
